## Implementation Complete! ✅

I have successfully completed all three phases of the implementation plan to reduce cognitive complexity in `CookSessionAdapter::update_session`.

### Summary of Changes

- 7 inline debug!() calls creating mental overhead
- Nested if-let block with business logic interleaved with logging
- Update loop mixed with cache update logic

**After (7 lines, significantly reduced complexity):**
```rust
#[tracing::instrument(skip(self, update))]
async fn update_session(&self, update: CookSessionUpdate) -> Result<()> {
    let Some(id) = &*self.current_session.lock().await else {
        return Ok(());
    };

    let unified_updates = Self::cook_update_to_unified(update);
    self.apply_unified_updates(id, unified_updates).await
}
```
